HEADWORD: Melopiano
<hw>Mel`o*pi*a"no</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>me`los</grk> song + E. <ets>piano</ets>.]</ety> <def>A piano having
a mechanical attachment which enables the player to prolong the notes at
will.</def>⟦br⟧
